58.8	Carol_Gilligan	Carol Gilligan	Carol Gilligan (born November 28, 1936) is an American feminist, ethicist, and psychologist best known for her work with and against Lawrence Kohlberg on ethical community and ethical relationships, and certain subject-object problems in ethics. She is currently a Professor at New York University and a Visiting Professor at the University of Cambridge. She is best known for her 1982 work, In a Different Voice.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/de/Carol_and_James_Gilligan_P1010970.jpg/220px-Carol_and_James_Gilligan_P1010970.jpg
